      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "especially during IBD blocks can come in very slowly from peers. without being able to know what a message is until we've downloaded it, it makes it difficult to know if a peer is stalling block download / IBD, as a block may be coming in, but take a while to download each block. When it was possible to process the message header before the message arrived, I was using this to work out the stallers in a better way than the current stall logic.",
